  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T028-08 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-09-30): 5 of 6 `PrecedentAdminEndpointsTests` pass; only `PostPrecedent_AsAdmin_Returns_201_WithTentativeStatus` fails. The endpoint returns 201 (matching the outer assertion) but the Moq verification on `CreateTentativeAsync` records zero invocations. The dispatching is "working" — just not the way the test expects.

      Hypothesis 1: Phase 1 task 011 (RB-T028-03/04/05/06 cluster fix) may have already resolved this if the root cause was conditional-registration + unconditional-endpoint-mapping. Verify by re-enabling this test post-011 and running before any new work.

      Hypothesis 2: Signature drift (`CreateTentativeAsync` renamed to `CreatePendingAsync` or `CreatePrecedentAsync`). If so, the test's Moq expectation is stale — update test to match production reality. NOT a production bug; mark `repaired` via test-only edit.

      Hypothesis 3: Genuine production gap — the handler returns 201 without invoking the service. Investigate and fix.

      Sibling project coordination: `ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1` is the named owner per ledger; coordinate if production-side change required.
    </background>
